1
00:03:23,160 --> 00:03:25,240
There's no way you can make me
get engaged to Ake.

2
00:03:25,320 --> 00:03:26,160
Don't do this.

3
00:03:26,240 --> 00:03:27,600
Let me live my life!

4
00:03:27,680 --> 00:03:28,600
- Ma'am?
- Pen!

5
00:03:28,680 --> 00:03:29,560
- Mom!
- Pen!

6
00:03:29,640 --> 00:03:31,120
I'll do it for you.

7
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:33,720
PREVIOUSLY

8
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:36,120
You know why I got engaged to you.

9
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:37,280
Where are you going?

10
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:39,720
Are you going to keep running
from me for the rest of your life?

11
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:41,800
We don't have to see each other again.

12
00:03:41,880 --> 00:03:43,480
This is Ake's and Dao's engagement party.

13
00:03:44,280 --> 00:03:45,520
Did you hear him?

14
00:03:46,640 --> 00:03:47,960
I'm now engaged to Ake.

15
00:03:48,040 --> 00:03:49,200
Petch, get ready.

16
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:50,800
You can work here without me, Dam.

17
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:53,840
Are you crazy? We've come this far.

18
00:03:53,920 --> 00:03:56,000
How could you abandon me like this?

19
00:03:56,520 --> 00:03:57,760
Give me a break, man.

20
00:03:57,840 --> 00:03:58,960
If I force myself to sing,

21
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:01,280
it won't sound good anyway.

22
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:05,360
I would like to thank all of you

23
00:04:05,880 --> 00:04:07,440
for coming tonight.

24
00:04:08,320 --> 00:04:10,080
The next song

25
00:04:11,040 --> 00:04:12,680
is my most beloved song.

26
00:04:24,920 --> 00:04:29,880
<i>I wish I knew if I ever crossed your mind</i>

27
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:36,280
<i>I wish I knew if you heard the whisper</i>

28
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:42,920
<i>For my heart is crying out my love</i>
<i>It's deep and true</i>

29
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:48,080
<i>But never reaching you</i>

30
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:54,200
<i>I know that it simply cannot be</i>

31
00:04:55,200 --> 00:05:00,160
<i>And I never want to cause you misery</i>

32
00:05:01,520 --> 00:05:07,000
<i>I'm just an ordinary man</i>
<i>Worth nothing at all</i>

33
00:05:07,520 --> 00:05:12,760
<i>And I never want to make</i>
<i>Your teardrops fall</i>

34
00:05:14,200 --> 00:05:18,520
<i>You are out of reach</i>

35
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:24,640
<i>Is it a crime that I need you?</i>

36
00:05:26,440 --> 00:05:30,560
<i>Please let me know for sure</i>

37
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:36,760
<i>That you're the one I've been waiting for</i>

38
00:05:37,280 --> 00:05:42,280
<i>How much longer can I bear this pain?</i>

39
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:48,280
<i>How much longer must I wait in vain?</i>

40
00:05:49,320 --> 00:05:54,880
<i>I really don't know what move to make</i>

41
00:05:55,480 --> 00:06:00,880
<i>To end this heartache</i>
<i>And say that I love you</i>

42
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:07,280
The song was so beautiful.

43
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:08,640
Thank you.

44
00:06:09,760 --> 00:06:11,800
- We'll go ahead.
- Bye.

45
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:13,960
Dao!

46
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:17,440
Who's the singer? He's so cool.

47
00:06:17,520 --> 00:06:18,600
Very handsome.

48
00:06:19,200 --> 00:06:21,360
Oh. He's our pub singer.

49
00:06:21,440 --> 00:06:24,720
I thought you were playing the piano
for Ake to sing.

50
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:26,200
He can't sing.

51
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:28,240
Are you guys leaving?

52
00:06:28,320 --> 00:06:29,400
Yes.

53
00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:33,880
I wanted to say goodbye to Ake,
but he's nowhere to be found.

54
00:06:43,840 --> 00:06:44,880
Damn it!

55
00:06:45,520 --> 00:06:46,480
Sir…

56
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:47,440
Get out!

57
00:06:51,720 --> 00:06:52,600
Mud.

58
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:54,880
You stay.

59
00:06:57,080 --> 00:06:57,920
Yes, sir.

60
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:00,480
Tell Petch

61
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:02,280
and his friends

62
00:07:03,520 --> 00:07:04,920
to see me here.

63
00:07:07,280 --> 00:07:09,320
I'll sort them out.

64
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:11,480
- Yes, sir.
- Go now!

65
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:14,760
Petch.

66
00:07:14,840 --> 00:07:16,880
You were amazing, dude.

67
00:07:16,960 --> 00:07:19,280
When you were singing, I almost cried.

68
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:24,720
Amazing.

69
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:28,720
If I weren't the one
who offered you this gig,

70
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:32,320
I would think
that you and Ms. Dao had an affair.

71
00:07:32,920 --> 00:07:34,120
You're ridiculous.

72
00:07:34,200 --> 00:07:35,840
Am I?

73
00:07:35,920 --> 00:07:39,560
Petch and Ms. Dao
performed harmoniously together.

74
00:07:40,480 --> 00:07:43,200
I wonder what Ake thought about it.

75
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:47,440
Ake wants to see you all.

76
00:07:47,520 --> 00:07:48,880
What is it about, brother?

77
00:07:48,960 --> 00:07:49,960
My name is Mud.

78
00:07:50,480 --> 00:07:52,480
I'm the manager, not your brother.

79
00:07:52,560 --> 00:07:54,160
Okay, sir. I'll keep that in mind.

80
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:56,400
Go on. The boss is waiting.

81
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:57,840
Of course.

82
00:07:58,600 --> 00:07:59,520
We're coming.

83
00:08:03,640 --> 00:08:05,440
Petch, wait.

84
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:10,600
How do we know
that Akekaphol won't trap us in there?

85
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:12,280
We've come this far.

86
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:13,720
What are you afraid of?

87
00:08:15,960 --> 00:08:17,320
Petch, I'm coming with you.

88
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:20,200
Can you stay out of this?

89
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:22,720
Damn.

90
00:08:25,560 --> 00:08:27,160
Dao, you're here.

91
00:08:27,760 --> 00:08:28,680
Who are you?

92
00:08:28,760 --> 00:08:30,800
I'm Sai Kaew, Damrong's younger sister.

93
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:33,120
We'd better go help Petch.

94
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:34,039
What's going on?

95
00:08:34,640 --> 00:08:36,360
Akekaphol asked to see Petch.

96
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:37,960
I'm afraid something bad might happen.

97
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:40,679
Thank you. I'll take care of this.

98
00:08:45,280 --> 00:08:46,880
- What's up?
- You again.

99
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:49,920
- Get out of my way!
- Ouch!

100
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:50,840
Hey!

101
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:55,240
Oh, I wonder what the latest happening is.

102
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:33,160
Bang!

103
00:09:38,680 --> 00:09:39,920
It was just acting.

104
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:46,360
Just so you guys would understand

105
00:09:47,320 --> 00:09:49,560
the kind of fate that awaits

106
00:09:50,600 --> 00:09:52,360
those who go against me.

107
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:54,960
Ake.

108
00:09:57,160 --> 00:09:58,400
Don't do anything to Petch.

109
00:09:58,480 --> 00:09:59,600
Dao.

110
00:10:00,400 --> 00:10:01,560
I didn't do anything.

111
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:04,480
You haven't. What about your plans, then?

112
00:10:04,560 --> 00:10:05,480
Hey.

113
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:07,200
Stay out of it.

114
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:10,320
Why did you call Ake and Damrong in?

115
00:10:11,080 --> 00:10:14,720
I just wanted to thank Petch

116
00:10:16,280 --> 00:10:18,040
for singing so beautifully

117
00:10:18,560 --> 00:10:19,800
at our engagement party.

118
00:10:23,240 --> 00:10:26,200
I also wanted to congratulate Petch

119
00:10:27,280 --> 00:10:28,960
on his new job.

120
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:34,760
I hope you're great enough

121
00:10:36,400 --> 00:10:38,000
to not humiliate Dao,

122
00:10:38,760 --> 00:10:39,880
to not let her down,

123
00:10:41,320 --> 00:10:42,720
or ruin her reputation.

124
00:10:49,840 --> 00:10:50,720
Yes.

125
00:10:51,360 --> 00:10:52,240
Likewise.

126
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:54,480
I hope you're good enough

127
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:57,520
not to bring your fiancée…

128
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:01,320
down.

129
00:11:18,400 --> 00:11:19,400
Petch.

130
00:11:19,920 --> 00:11:21,600
It's such a small world, right?

131
00:11:23,560 --> 00:11:28,240
You, Dao, and Akekaphol keep
crossing each other's paths.

132
00:11:29,520 --> 00:11:30,440
Petch.

133
00:11:35,160 --> 00:11:36,600
Here's to you

134
00:11:37,240 --> 00:11:39,200
for manning up and facing your old wound.

135
00:11:54,120 --> 00:11:55,640
It's just like what you said.

136
00:11:57,280 --> 00:11:59,160
We can't run away from our feelings.

137
00:12:01,040 --> 00:12:03,120
The best we can do

138
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:05,360
is to accept them

139
00:12:05,920 --> 00:12:06,920
and live.

140
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:12,400
You are a changed man.

141
00:12:13,720 --> 00:12:15,560
We need to live and learn, don't we?

142
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:18,840
Moreover,

143
00:12:20,120 --> 00:12:23,560
I need to do a better job
of separating my work

144
00:12:23,640 --> 00:12:24,680
and personal life.

145
00:12:25,280 --> 00:12:28,600
I'm glad that you have come
to your senses.

146
00:12:30,040 --> 00:12:31,320
Let's wait for Berm

147
00:12:32,520 --> 00:12:33,960
and get the band back together.

148
00:12:34,480 --> 00:12:35,840
- Okay?
- Yes.

149
00:12:35,920 --> 00:12:37,280
- Okay?
- Yes!

150
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:38,880
All right. Come on.

151
00:12:40,200 --> 00:12:42,040
Here's to our future.

152
00:12:43,520 --> 00:12:44,840
Right.

153
00:12:54,880 --> 00:12:55,720
Dao.

154
00:12:58,560 --> 00:13:00,000
Wait for me.

155
00:13:04,480 --> 00:13:07,720
Don't forget to have Petch
bring his resume,

156
00:13:08,640 --> 00:13:10,000
so we can register him properly.

157
00:13:10,920 --> 00:13:14,080
He will also receive a monthly salary
and other benefits.

158
00:13:16,680 --> 00:13:18,000
Are you the real Ake?

159
00:13:19,040 --> 00:13:20,320
Why?

160
00:13:20,840 --> 00:13:22,760
Are you saying I'm faking it?

161
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:24,200
That's not what I'm saying.

162
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:29,360
I'm just doubting
this kindness towards Petch.

163
00:13:31,280 --> 00:13:32,400
To be honest, Dao,

164
00:13:33,720 --> 00:13:35,000
I'm not a good person.

165
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:38,760
So you're still bitter about it.

166
00:13:40,960 --> 00:13:41,800
Dao.

167
00:13:42,520 --> 00:13:43,680
You're overthinking it.

168
00:13:44,320 --> 00:13:46,400
I've put everything behind us.

169
00:13:47,120 --> 00:13:48,520
I won't keep thinking about it.

170
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:51,680
Then what are you saying?

171
00:13:51,760 --> 00:13:53,440
My concern is for our business, Dao.

172
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:55,920
The reason I'm being nice

173
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:58,800
is that I think Petch will be a hit.

174
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:03,040
He can be our pub's top singer.

175
00:14:03,720 --> 00:14:04,760
Let's just say

176
00:14:05,360 --> 00:14:06,760
it's mutually beneficial.

177
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:11,360
That's why I said I'm not a good man.

178
00:14:13,880 --> 00:14:15,200
I wasn't prepared

179
00:14:15,920 --> 00:14:17,800
for this brand new Ake.

180
00:14:19,840 --> 00:14:21,120
There is one thing

181
00:14:21,680 --> 00:14:23,320
that will never change.

182
00:14:44,680 --> 00:14:45,880
I love you, Dao.

183
00:14:54,800 --> 00:14:55,840
Good night,

184
00:14:56,520 --> 00:14:57,600
my fiancée.

185
00:15:23,280 --> 00:15:25,920
MUD

186
00:15:26,520 --> 00:15:28,880
Why are you calling, Mud?
I'm not in the mood.

187
00:15:29,400 --> 00:15:30,440
Don't talk.

188
00:15:31,320 --> 00:15:33,480
Go get me some pretty faces.

189
00:15:34,040 --> 00:15:36,080
I don't care how much it costs.

190
00:15:57,400 --> 00:16:01,440
<i>You are out of reach</i>

191
00:16:02,160 --> 00:16:07,360
<i>Is it a crime that I need you?</i>

192
00:16:09,320 --> 00:16:14,080
<i>Please let me know for sure</i>

193
00:16:14,160 --> 00:16:19,360
<i>That you're the one I've been waiting for</i>

194
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:24,920
<i>How much longer can I bear this pain?</i>

195
00:16:26,440 --> 00:16:31,520
<i>How much longer must I wait in vain?</i>

196
00:16:32,360 --> 00:16:38,240
<i>I really don't know what move to make</i>

197
00:16:38,320 --> 00:16:41,840
<i>To end this heartache</i>
<i>And say that I love you</i>

198
00:16:41,920 --> 00:16:44,920
This is my number and Petch's.

199
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:47,720
You can call us for other gigs.

200
00:17:00,440 --> 00:17:02,360
A ghost!

201
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:04,200
It's me, Dammy!

202
00:17:04,280 --> 00:17:05,280
Gosh.

203
00:17:05,359 --> 00:17:07,000
I thought it was a ghost!

204
00:17:07,079 --> 00:17:09,079
Stop being ridiculous.

205
00:17:09,160 --> 00:17:11,119
You're such a jerk.

206
00:17:11,640 --> 00:17:12,800
Are we really related?

207
00:17:12,880 --> 00:17:15,040
Did our parents get a puppy as my brother?

208
00:17:15,119 --> 00:17:17,800
Hey! Why move the curtain?

209
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:21,000
I just want to say good night to Petch.

210
00:17:22,520 --> 00:17:24,560
Stop it. Let's go to bed.

211
00:17:30,520 --> 00:17:31,800
Who's calling this late?

212
00:17:34,920 --> 00:17:35,800
Hello.

213
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:38,160
<i>Petch. It's me.</i>

214
00:17:39,040 --> 00:17:39,920
Dao?

215
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:42,880
How do you know my number?

216
00:17:43,960 --> 00:17:45,280
Damrong gave it to me.

217
00:17:46,280 --> 00:17:47,600
Anything I can help you with?

218
00:17:47,680 --> 00:17:48,600
Petch.

219
00:17:48,680 --> 00:17:50,600
I'm afraid that you'll be paid late.

220
00:17:50,680 --> 00:17:53,240
Please come in tomorrow
to fill out the application,

221
00:17:53,320 --> 00:17:54,920
so you can get paid.

222
00:17:55,880 --> 00:17:57,760
Okay, thank you.

223
00:17:58,280 --> 00:18:00,520
Petch, dear, let's go to bed.

224
00:18:00,600 --> 00:18:01,960
- What the…
- Hey!

225
00:18:02,560 --> 00:18:05,080
Who was that, Petch? Sai Kaew?

226
00:18:05,160 --> 00:18:06,160
Yes.

227
00:18:07,160 --> 00:18:08,480
<i>We live together.</i>

228
00:18:09,080 --> 00:18:11,080
Me, Dam…

229
00:18:12,840 --> 00:18:14,200
and Sai.

230
00:18:14,280 --> 00:18:16,760
<i>Please feel free to talk, Dao.</i>

231
00:18:16,840 --> 00:18:19,080
The nuisance has been neutralized.

232
00:18:20,080 --> 00:18:23,360
Please tell Damrong to come in too.
I'm hanging up.

233
00:18:25,920 --> 00:18:27,640
Ouch!

234
00:18:30,040 --> 00:18:32,240
Hey, Ms. Dao. Why did you call so late?

235
00:18:32,320 --> 00:18:34,040
Don't forget that you're engaged.

236
00:18:35,960 --> 00:18:36,960
She has hung up.

237
00:18:37,560 --> 00:18:38,680
Oh, okay.

238
00:18:39,920 --> 00:18:41,960
Sai, you idiot!

239
00:18:42,760 --> 00:18:44,920
Love-drunk fool. What's wrong with you?

240
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:47,360
I don't like people hitting on Petch.

241
00:18:47,440 --> 00:18:49,240
Especially Ms. Dao.

242
00:18:49,840 --> 00:18:51,000
Sai.

243
00:18:51,080 --> 00:18:54,280
Dao called to tell Dam and me
to come to the office tomorrow.

244
00:18:54,960 --> 00:18:56,000
It's about work.

245
00:18:56,080 --> 00:18:57,760
It's not personal, Sai.

246
00:18:57,840 --> 00:18:58,680
Right.

247
00:18:59,520 --> 00:19:00,880
You'd better separate them.

248
00:19:02,960 --> 00:19:05,160
What about you? Do you separate them?

249
00:19:05,240 --> 00:19:06,800
What were you and Dao?

250
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:09,400
Why did you break up? Tell me now.

251
00:19:09,480 --> 00:19:12,680
- Sai, you…
- What? Don't stop me, Dammy.

252
00:19:13,320 --> 00:19:14,200
Petch.

253
00:19:14,280 --> 00:19:18,760
If you don't tell me straight today,
I'll scream it out!

254
00:19:18,840 --> 00:19:20,840
- Why--
- Shut up.

255
00:19:20,920 --> 00:19:23,120
I'll say it one last time, Sai.

256
00:19:25,680 --> 00:19:27,840
The past is the past.

257
00:19:28,720 --> 00:19:30,400
Dao is engaged now.

258
00:19:30,480 --> 00:19:32,360
I don't wish to chase after someone taken.

259
00:19:34,400 --> 00:19:35,320
Petch…

260
00:19:38,280 --> 00:19:39,880
I'm relieved for now.

261
00:19:42,600 --> 00:19:43,840
Where are you off to?

262
00:19:45,320 --> 00:19:47,360
I'll play the guitar.

263
00:19:47,880 --> 00:19:49,000
I can't sleep.

264
00:19:50,680 --> 00:19:52,960
I'll keep you company, then.

265
00:19:53,040 --> 00:19:56,080
- Come here, you.
- Hey.

266
00:19:56,160 --> 00:19:57,000
Hey!

267
00:19:57,080 --> 00:19:58,680
Keep him company?

268
00:19:58,760 --> 00:20:02,000
You'll be more of a nuisance
than anything.

269
00:20:02,880 --> 00:20:04,200
Is that so?

270
00:20:04,280 --> 00:20:06,120
Then I'll annoy you to death first.

271
00:20:06,880 --> 00:20:08,160
- Here!
- Hey!

272
00:20:08,760 --> 00:20:11,240
- I'm your brother.
- So?

273
00:20:11,320 --> 00:20:12,440
Stop it!

274
00:20:13,040 --> 00:20:14,240
Go!

275
00:20:15,760 --> 00:20:17,680
<i>I wish I knew…</i>

276
00:20:17,760 --> 00:20:18,720
Hey!

277
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:20,800
What are you singing?

278
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:25,720
Don't you know

279
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:27,640
that I hate that song?

280
00:20:29,680 --> 00:20:30,760
Please calm down, sir.

281
00:20:32,440 --> 00:20:33,840
They're useless.

282
00:20:34,360 --> 00:20:35,400
Get out, all of you!

283
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:37,600
Leave! Go!

284
00:20:40,920 --> 00:20:42,360
Engagement day?

285
00:20:43,120 --> 00:20:44,360
A day of happiness?

286
00:20:45,440 --> 00:20:46,960
What a day!

287
00:20:47,040 --> 00:20:48,840
- Damn it!
- Ake, sir.

288
00:20:48,920 --> 00:20:51,520
- Ake! Please stop, sir.
- Let go!

289
00:20:53,160 --> 00:20:54,960
If you hate Petch that much,

290
00:20:55,480 --> 00:20:56,720
just tell me

291
00:20:57,240 --> 00:20:58,800
and I'll get rid of him.

292
00:20:58,880 --> 00:21:00,240
We can't do that!

293
00:21:02,160 --> 00:21:03,520
If we do that,

294
00:21:04,600 --> 00:21:07,040
Dao will distance herself from me.

295
00:21:08,960 --> 00:21:10,080
Are you

296
00:21:10,160 --> 00:21:11,800
putting on an act

297
00:21:11,880 --> 00:21:13,640
to stay in Dao's good graces?

298
00:21:13,720 --> 00:21:15,080
Damn right I am.

299
00:21:17,520 --> 00:21:18,360
For now,

300
00:21:19,840 --> 00:21:21,120
I have to let him be.

301
00:21:23,120 --> 00:21:24,120
But you

302
00:21:25,120 --> 00:21:27,120
will need to follow my order.

303
00:21:28,280 --> 00:21:29,120
All right.

304
00:21:29,720 --> 00:21:31,000
What is it, sir?

305
00:21:31,080 --> 00:21:32,480
Go find out

306
00:21:33,800 --> 00:21:35,400
where he lives

307
00:21:36,680 --> 00:21:37,880
and what he does

308
00:21:41,960 --> 00:21:44,240
so we can get rid of him subtly

309
00:21:46,640 --> 00:21:48,320
that Dao won't see it coming.

310
00:22:23,800 --> 00:22:25,320
- What are you doing?
- Hey!

311
00:22:25,400 --> 00:22:26,920
Hey. Ouch!

312
00:22:28,360 --> 00:22:29,240
Damn you!

313
00:22:29,320 --> 00:22:31,360
I hope the universe gets back at you!

314
00:22:41,800 --> 00:22:44,480
Wow, <i>patongko</i>, my favorite!

315
00:22:44,560 --> 00:22:46,280
Here, give me that.

316
00:22:46,360 --> 00:22:49,080
Here, my foot! This is for Petch!

317
00:22:49,680 --> 00:22:50,800
I'm your brother.

318
00:22:50,880 --> 00:22:52,880
I know. That's why I won't give you any.

319
00:22:53,400 --> 00:22:54,720
Ungrateful sister! Give me that!

320
00:22:54,800 --> 00:22:56,600
No! This is for Petch!

321
00:22:57,960 --> 00:22:59,240
- You!
- Hey.

322
00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:01,240
Why are you fighting?

323
00:23:01,760 --> 00:23:04,040
Dammy started it, Petch!

324
00:23:04,120 --> 00:23:06,480
He's also stealing your <i>patongko</i>.

325
00:23:08,400 --> 00:23:09,560
He doesn't have to steal.

326
00:23:10,480 --> 00:23:11,480
Let him have it all.

327
00:23:15,040 --> 00:23:17,440
Trying to impress him,
but he is not impressed.

328
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:19,760
Dammy!

329
00:23:19,840 --> 00:23:23,440
I hope the universe gets back at you
the way it will that damned man.

330
00:23:24,080 --> 00:23:25,200
Damned man?

331
00:23:25,280 --> 00:23:28,840
Just when I got back
from buying this <i>patongko</i>,

332
00:23:28,920 --> 00:23:31,680
I saw a guy sneaking a peek at our place.

333
00:23:31,760 --> 00:23:34,520
I saw him taking your photos, Petch.

334
00:23:35,120 --> 00:23:36,000
Really?

335
00:23:36,080 --> 00:23:37,880
Really! Why would I make that up?

336
00:23:37,960 --> 00:23:43,280
When I asked him what he was up to,
he pushed me and ran away.

337
00:23:44,520 --> 00:23:47,200
Why would he do that?

338
00:23:47,960 --> 00:23:50,360
How would I know? I'm not his wife.

339
00:23:51,240 --> 00:23:53,240
- You're talking back?
- Come on!

340
00:23:53,320 --> 00:23:54,600
I'll fight back!

341
00:23:55,280 --> 00:23:58,600
I'm asking nicely.
Can't you answer nicely?

342
00:23:59,200 --> 00:24:00,720
I did answer nicely.

343
00:24:00,800 --> 00:24:02,840
How on earth would I know?

344
00:24:04,120 --> 00:24:05,600
Could it be

345
00:24:06,520 --> 00:24:08,800
a loan shark, Petch?

346
00:24:10,240 --> 00:24:11,120
It couldn't be.

347
00:24:13,120 --> 00:24:14,920
Maybe it's just a coincidence.

348
00:24:16,120 --> 00:24:17,040
That's right.

349
00:24:17,640 --> 00:24:21,520
He might be taking pictures
of other people, not Petch.

350
00:24:22,040 --> 00:24:23,800
Don't imagine things.

351
00:24:23,880 --> 00:24:25,480
I know what I saw.

352
00:24:26,120 --> 00:24:27,920
Enough of that.

353
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:29,680
Let's go to the office.

354
00:24:33,800 --> 00:24:34,880
Be careful, Petch.

355
00:24:34,960 --> 00:24:37,000
By the way…

356
00:24:38,320 --> 00:24:39,960
- Hey!
- I'm taking these.

357
00:24:40,040 --> 00:24:42,320
These things will make you cough.

358
00:24:42,400 --> 00:24:44,440
Dammy! You're one to talk!

359
00:24:50,880 --> 00:24:52,040
Sai Kaew!

360
00:24:54,200 --> 00:24:55,320
Where are you off to?

361
00:24:56,080 --> 00:24:57,320
Changing into my uniform, ma'am.

362
00:24:57,840 --> 00:24:59,120
What about Petch and Damrong?

363
00:25:00,160 --> 00:25:01,440
Do you really have to ask?

364
00:25:01,520 --> 00:25:05,120
They followed whatever you said,
Ms. Natedao.

365
00:25:05,200 --> 00:25:06,200
That's nice.

366
00:25:06,800 --> 00:25:10,160
You're such a polite person.
You called me miss and ma'am.

367
00:25:10,920 --> 00:25:11,840
But…

368
00:25:11,920 --> 00:25:13,800
But what?

369
00:25:14,840 --> 00:25:16,760
Your expression and tone of voice
say otherwise.

370
00:25:17,560 --> 00:25:19,280
They betray your true feelings

371
00:25:19,360 --> 00:25:20,680
and they aren't nice.

372
00:25:22,240 --> 00:25:23,360
Fix it.

373
00:25:23,960 --> 00:25:25,840
Be polite and sincere

374
00:25:26,520 --> 00:25:28,560
and people will love you

375
00:25:29,080 --> 00:25:30,520
without you trying at all.

376
00:25:38,080 --> 00:25:38,920
You…

377
00:25:39,600 --> 00:25:40,840
Ms. Little Barbie.

378
00:25:40,920 --> 00:25:43,760
Why would I be nice to someone
stealing Petch from me?

379
00:25:44,280 --> 00:25:45,360
She's out of her mind.

380
00:26:03,520 --> 00:26:05,360
Dao, you're here.

381
00:26:06,440 --> 00:26:07,920
Have you got the documents?

382
00:26:08,520 --> 00:26:11,320
Yes. The admin staff gave us

383
00:26:11,400 --> 00:26:15,080
application forms
and other questionnaires.

384
00:26:16,840 --> 00:26:19,280
Once you're done with those,
please give them to me.

385
00:26:19,360 --> 00:26:20,560
Of course.

386
00:26:28,800 --> 00:26:32,960
Petch, are you really going
to ignore her completely?

387
00:26:34,520 --> 00:26:35,440
Shut up.

388
00:26:36,160 --> 00:26:37,120
Let's finish these.

389
00:26:39,760 --> 00:26:42,800
Keep putting on that act, love-drunk.

390
00:26:42,880 --> 00:26:44,280
I can see right through you.

391
00:26:58,160 --> 00:26:59,120
<i>Dao, dear.</i>

392
00:26:59,800 --> 00:27:01,320
<i>I'm seeing my uncle now.</i>

393
00:27:02,360 --> 00:27:05,160
I can't go to lunch with you today.

394
00:27:05,240 --> 00:27:06,760
It's okay.

395
00:27:06,840 --> 00:27:09,920
Please let Mr. Sompob know
that in three days,

396
00:27:10,000 --> 00:27:11,720
I will pitch a new project to him.

397
00:27:11,800 --> 00:27:13,880
Wow, Dao.

398
00:27:13,960 --> 00:27:17,880
Your passion will make you
his favorite instead of me.

399
00:27:18,480 --> 00:27:20,160
I don't think about that.

400
00:27:20,240 --> 00:27:22,200
I just want to work
to my fullest potential

401
00:27:22,280 --> 00:27:23,880
and maintain his trust in me.

402
00:27:23,960 --> 00:27:24,840
Dao.

403
00:27:25,360 --> 00:27:27,040
I also believe in you.

404
00:27:27,720 --> 00:27:31,960
But I want to make sure you follow
the company's new hire protocol.

405
00:27:32,040 --> 00:27:33,400
What is it?

406
00:27:34,000 --> 00:27:37,720
Last month,
there was a fugitive working at our pub.

407
00:27:38,320 --> 00:27:40,280
It was pure chaos, Dao.

408
00:27:40,800 --> 00:27:44,480
I want you to be more strict
when it comes to hiring new staff.

409
00:27:45,560 --> 00:27:47,240
<i>Let's not move on</i>

410
00:27:47,760 --> 00:27:49,040
<i>with anyone with a record.</i>

411
00:27:51,680 --> 00:27:54,400
<i>Dao, are you all right?</i>
<i>Why aren't you saying anything?</i>

412
00:27:54,920 --> 00:27:57,240
Oh, it's nothing.

413
00:27:57,320 --> 00:27:58,440
I understand.

414
00:27:59,040 --> 00:28:00,480
<i>Is there anything else?</i>

415
00:28:00,560 --> 00:28:01,960
That's it for now.

416
00:28:02,600 --> 00:28:04,880
I miss you, Dao.

417
00:28:05,560 --> 00:28:07,720
I have to go back to work.

418
00:28:12,480 --> 00:28:14,200
If he finds out about Petch,

419
00:28:14,840 --> 00:28:16,000
he'll make a fuss.

420
00:28:22,600 --> 00:28:24,960
"Have you ever been imprisoned?"

421
00:28:25,040 --> 00:28:27,440
Petch, what's your answer
for this question?

422
00:28:28,480 --> 00:28:29,440
Let me see.

423
00:28:32,240 --> 00:28:33,400
"Yes, for homicide."

424
00:28:33,480 --> 00:28:35,760
Petch, are you out of your mind?

425
00:28:35,840 --> 00:28:37,560
Do you want me to lie again?

426
00:28:39,040 --> 00:28:40,200
Shut up! Be quiet.

427
00:28:42,240 --> 00:28:44,720
If someone hears this,
we'll both lose our jobs.

428
00:28:44,800 --> 00:28:47,800
Dao knows
that I was in the training center.

429
00:28:50,040 --> 00:28:50,920
Are you serious?

430
00:28:51,000 --> 00:28:52,800
She went to see my dad

431
00:28:53,400 --> 00:28:54,640
and found out about it.

432
00:28:55,400 --> 00:28:58,200
It's no use to lie.

433
00:29:02,320 --> 00:29:04,320
Can I just bang my head against the wall?

434
00:29:04,400 --> 00:29:05,760
Petch, wait! Stop!

435
00:29:06,840 --> 00:29:09,440
- Petch, don't--
- Dammy! Come here.

436
00:29:09,520 --> 00:29:10,640
Let's go eat <i>som tam!</i>

437
00:29:10,720 --> 00:29:12,080
Don't mess with me now.

438
00:29:12,160 --> 00:29:14,040
Hey! Dammy!

439
00:29:14,120 --> 00:29:16,840
We need to reserve a table
before it's crowded.

440
00:29:18,240 --> 00:29:19,720
- Here!
- Hey!

441
00:29:19,800 --> 00:29:22,320
We're on the verge of losing our jobs!

442
00:29:22,400 --> 00:29:24,080
What? Why is that?

443
00:29:24,160 --> 00:29:28,040
Petch filled out the application form
and said he had a record.

444
00:29:28,640 --> 00:29:29,600
I see.

445
00:29:29,680 --> 00:29:30,720
That's good.

446
00:29:31,920 --> 00:29:34,320
What? Petch wrote that he had a record?

447
00:29:34,400 --> 00:29:35,240
Hey!

448
00:29:36,840 --> 00:29:38,080
Shut up, Sai!

449
00:29:39,120 --> 00:29:39,960
Yuck!

450
00:29:40,040 --> 00:29:43,360
Your hand is so salty!
Is that a hand or a fish sauce bottle?

451
00:29:43,440 --> 00:29:45,320
Sai, you keep your mouth shut.

452
00:29:45,400 --> 00:29:48,280
Help me think of a way
to get him out of this situation.

453
00:29:48,360 --> 00:29:50,720
He would have reached out to Dao by now.

454
00:29:57,160 --> 00:29:58,720
Hey, Sai.

455
00:29:58,800 --> 00:30:00,160
Are you into black magic?

456
00:30:00,240 --> 00:30:04,680
Are you insane? At this point,
we can't do anything but pray.

457
00:30:05,480 --> 00:30:06,400
Come on!

458
00:30:07,200 --> 00:30:08,440
<i>Sathu.</i>

459
00:30:09,040 --> 00:30:12,160
I wish for Petch not to be fired.

460
00:30:16,320 --> 00:30:18,520
- I don't think it will work.
- It will.

461
00:30:23,400 --> 00:30:25,760
Please sit down
and we'll discuss your salary.

462
00:30:28,000 --> 00:30:30,160
I think you should check
my documents first.

463
00:30:31,520 --> 00:30:32,640
Why?

464
00:30:33,240 --> 00:30:35,880
Just in case there are things
that disqualify me,

465
00:30:35,960 --> 00:30:37,360
so you wouldn't have to waste your time.

466
00:30:38,920 --> 00:30:41,280
You are skilled and have a great voice.

467
00:30:41,800 --> 00:30:43,000
Why wouldn't I hire you?

468
00:30:49,520 --> 00:30:50,400
Here.

469
00:30:51,280 --> 00:30:53,320
I answered the questionnaire.

470
00:30:54,000 --> 00:30:54,920
YES, FOR HOMICIDE

471
00:30:55,000 --> 00:30:57,400
I was charged with homicide.

472
00:31:02,240 --> 00:31:04,480
I know that. And?

473
00:31:05,080 --> 00:31:06,280
I don't want to hide it.

474
00:31:07,280 --> 00:31:09,280
That's why I wanted to check with you

475
00:31:10,040 --> 00:31:12,000
as a director,

476
00:31:12,600 --> 00:31:13,520
not a friend.

477
00:31:14,760 --> 00:31:15,760
A friend?

478
00:31:18,760 --> 00:31:20,120
You're engaged.

479
00:31:21,720 --> 00:31:23,640
Let's say we're ex-friends.

480
00:31:26,240 --> 00:31:27,080
That's right.

481
00:31:28,600 --> 00:31:30,200
Let's be just employer

482
00:31:30,280 --> 00:31:31,480
and employee.

483
00:31:43,400 --> 00:31:44,400
This looks fine.

484
00:31:45,200 --> 00:31:46,760
You wrote down the truth.

485
00:31:47,720 --> 00:31:48,560
Good.

486
00:31:49,560 --> 00:31:50,480
Thanks.

487
00:31:50,560 --> 00:31:51,720
Hold on.

488
00:31:54,600 --> 00:31:55,680
What about your salary?

489
00:31:55,760 --> 00:31:58,440
I'll take whatever. You decide.

490
00:32:17,120 --> 00:32:18,280
Petch just left.

491
00:32:21,040 --> 00:32:22,240
Okay. Here goes nothing.

492
00:32:23,240 --> 00:32:24,560
Hey, Dammy!

493
00:32:24,640 --> 00:32:25,720
Wait for me!

494
00:32:28,600 --> 00:32:29,480
Dao!

495
00:32:33,880 --> 00:32:36,280
Why did you tear up
Petch's application form?

496
00:32:36,880 --> 00:32:40,320
You don't agree
with what Petch wrote, right?

497
00:32:41,560 --> 00:32:43,800
I don't mind that he has a record.

498
00:32:44,480 --> 00:32:45,680
But it might not be the case

499
00:32:46,360 --> 00:32:48,280
for other people.

500
00:32:49,840 --> 00:32:52,080
I was going to discuss it with you.

501
00:32:52,160 --> 00:32:53,800
Please help him, Dao.

502
00:32:54,320 --> 00:32:55,640
I'm begging you.

503
00:32:55,720 --> 00:32:57,000
You don't have to beg.

504
00:32:57,080 --> 00:32:59,280
I don't want a good guy like him
to lose this opportunity.

505
00:32:59,360 --> 00:33:00,640
What are you going to do?

506
00:33:00,720 --> 00:33:02,440
We need to work together.

507
00:33:03,560 --> 00:33:04,520
We?

508
00:33:05,040 --> 00:33:06,160
Right.

509
00:33:07,040 --> 00:33:09,880
Petch's record will be kept clean.

510
00:33:10,400 --> 00:33:11,240
Which is why

511
00:33:11,760 --> 00:33:14,360
I tore up his application form.

512
00:33:14,880 --> 00:33:16,400
I will write up a new one.

513
00:33:17,920 --> 00:33:20,720
Oh, you're amazing.

514
00:33:21,760 --> 00:33:22,960
I need both of you

515
00:33:23,560 --> 00:33:25,560
to stop Petch from telling anyone.

516
00:33:25,640 --> 00:33:26,680
Can you do that?

517
00:33:27,360 --> 00:33:28,480
Of course.

518
00:33:28,560 --> 00:33:29,520
Right?

519
00:33:30,040 --> 00:33:35,080
Totally. Don't worry. Dammy and I
won't let anything leave his mouth.

520
00:33:35,160 --> 00:33:36,480
Excellent.

521
00:33:36,560 --> 00:33:38,600
If Ake finds out about this,

522
00:33:39,120 --> 00:33:40,640
he will fire Petch.

523
00:33:56,960 --> 00:34:00,640
Damn it. It's my day off
and I had to come here for my makeup bag.

524
00:34:06,160 --> 00:34:07,440
Where is it?

525
00:34:14,080 --> 00:34:15,719
Where are you hiding?

526
00:34:19,400 --> 00:34:20,719
- Hey!
- You jerk!

527
00:34:20,800 --> 00:34:21,760
- Hey!
- Damn it.

528
00:34:21,840 --> 00:34:24,040
Aren't you too dramatic?

529
00:34:24,120 --> 00:34:25,840
Why did you sneak up on me?

530
00:34:25,920 --> 00:34:27,560
You scared me, Joke.

531
00:34:27,639 --> 00:34:28,840
Damn it.

532
00:34:28,920 --> 00:34:31,360
- Scared of an angel like me?
- Such nonsense.

533
00:34:32,880 --> 00:34:34,120
I found it.

534
00:34:36,920 --> 00:34:38,159
Wait.

535
00:34:39,520 --> 00:34:41,960
Where are you rushing to, my debtor?

536
00:34:42,480 --> 00:34:44,600
Debtor? Who is your debtor?

537
00:34:44,679 --> 00:34:46,400
It's Petch.

538
00:34:46,480 --> 00:34:48,639
He owes me a suit rental fee.

539
00:34:48,719 --> 00:34:49,760
You pay me now.

540
00:34:49,840 --> 00:34:51,679
- Wait.
- Hey.

541
00:34:51,760 --> 00:34:53,120
Look at me.

542
00:34:53,199 --> 00:34:55,400
My name is Sai Kaew, not Petch!

543
00:34:55,480 --> 00:34:56,920
"My name is Sai Kaew, not Petch!"

544
00:34:57,000 --> 00:35:00,400
Well, you two seem close to each other.

545
00:35:00,480 --> 00:35:04,120
To be honest, asking you to pay
is the same as asking Petch.

546
00:35:05,160 --> 00:35:06,120
Pay me now.

547
00:35:06,200 --> 00:35:09,160
Otherwise, we're staying here all night.

548
00:35:10,280 --> 00:35:12,000
Are you really not going?

549
00:35:12,080 --> 00:35:13,040
Am I a joke to you?

550
00:35:14,040 --> 00:35:15,360
Hurry up and pay.

551
00:35:15,880 --> 00:35:16,720
Don't make me angry.

552
00:35:17,760 --> 00:35:20,040
Okay. Now, I'm scared.

553
00:35:20,120 --> 00:35:22,680
Right. That's it.

554
00:35:22,760 --> 00:35:23,920
But…

555
00:35:24,560 --> 00:35:25,960
But?

556
00:35:26,040 --> 00:35:27,800
Can you close your eyes, Joke?

557
00:35:28,320 --> 00:35:31,240
I keep my money in my bra. I'm shy.

558
00:35:31,320 --> 00:35:32,640
What?

559
00:35:32,720 --> 00:35:34,920
- In your bra?
- Yes.

560
00:35:35,800 --> 00:35:39,800
Okay, all right. I'll close my eyes now.

561
00:35:40,760 --> 00:35:41,600
Okay.

562
00:35:41,680 --> 00:35:43,040
Don't take a peek

563
00:35:43,120 --> 00:35:45,680
or I'll curse you with ten lifetimes
of being broke!

564
00:35:45,760 --> 00:35:48,000
Hey! Aren't you being too harsh?

565
00:35:48,080 --> 00:35:51,240
Hey, my eyes are heavy now.

566
00:35:51,320 --> 00:35:52,360
Are they closed?

567
00:35:52,440 --> 00:35:53,880
They are.

568
00:35:53,960 --> 00:35:55,960
Hey. I heard a paper sound.

569
00:35:56,040 --> 00:35:58,520
Is that my money?

570
00:35:58,600 --> 00:36:00,440
Take this with interest.

571
00:36:00,520 --> 00:36:01,800
- Where is it?
- Here!

572
00:36:01,880 --> 00:36:03,120
Here you go!

573
00:36:03,200 --> 00:36:04,880
Sai Keaw! What's this for?

574
00:36:07,480 --> 00:36:08,320
Hey!

575
00:36:09,040 --> 00:36:10,400
- Here, take it.
- Ouch.

576
00:36:10,480 --> 00:36:13,080
- Hey!
- Bloodsucker!

577
00:36:13,920 --> 00:36:15,440
What the heck!

578
00:36:16,200 --> 00:36:18,000
How could you do this to me?

579
00:36:18,080 --> 00:36:19,840
I will have my revenge.

580
00:36:19,920 --> 00:36:21,760
Where are you going?

581
00:36:23,960 --> 00:36:25,560
I'm sorry.

582
00:36:25,640 --> 00:36:28,520
Why are you in such a hurry?
Hasn't your shift started?

583
00:36:28,600 --> 00:36:31,400
It's my day off today,
but I came to get my stuff.

584
00:36:32,560 --> 00:36:33,720
Sai Kaew!

585
00:36:33,800 --> 00:36:35,640
- I'm leaving now.
- Where are you going?

586
00:36:36,240 --> 00:36:38,440
Hey! Where are you running away to? Hey!

587
00:36:39,360 --> 00:36:40,920
Damn it.

588
00:36:41,000 --> 00:36:44,400
Tell the debtor, Petch,
to pay the suit rental fee.

589
00:36:44,480 --> 00:36:45,440
It has been too long!

590
00:36:45,520 --> 00:36:46,920
Suit rental fee?

591
00:36:48,280 --> 00:36:49,720
Petch owes Joke money?

592
00:36:52,000 --> 00:36:52,880
Hey.

593
00:36:58,320 --> 00:36:59,680
MANGO STICKY RICE JE OUM

594
00:36:59,760 --> 00:37:01,240
Thank you.

595
00:37:04,360 --> 00:37:05,840
Thai chicken rice, ready.

596
00:37:05,920 --> 00:37:07,360
Mango sticky rice, ready.

597
00:37:08,600 --> 00:37:09,640
Petch, darling.

598
00:37:09,720 --> 00:37:12,960
I'm throwing a party
to celebrate your new job today!

599
00:37:18,320 --> 00:37:19,760
To 8th Alley, please.

600
00:37:32,640 --> 00:37:34,960
Please park on the left side.

601
00:37:44,280 --> 00:37:45,200
Here you are.

602
00:37:45,280 --> 00:37:46,240
How much is it?

603
00:37:46,320 --> 00:37:47,360
Thirty baht.

604
00:37:47,440 --> 00:37:49,480
Okay. One second, please.

605
00:37:50,800 --> 00:37:51,640
Shoot.

606
00:37:52,480 --> 00:37:54,280
I only have a thousand bill.
Do you have change?

607
00:37:54,360 --> 00:37:55,200
No.

608
00:37:55,280 --> 00:37:56,600
Do you accept online payment?

609
00:37:56,680 --> 00:37:57,880
- No.
- What?

610
00:37:58,480 --> 00:37:59,680
No this and no that.

611
00:37:59,760 --> 00:38:02,280
You're not flexible for your customer.

612
00:38:02,360 --> 00:38:04,560
You don't work with a service mind at all.

613
00:38:06,760 --> 00:38:07,600
Listen.

614
00:38:09,480 --> 00:38:10,560
You're a customer.

615
00:38:10,640 --> 00:38:12,320
Shouldn't you prepare smaller bills?

616
00:38:12,920 --> 00:38:14,600
You're putting all the blame
on taxi bikers.

617
00:38:15,120 --> 00:38:16,280
We're humans too!

618
00:38:17,080 --> 00:38:18,680
When did I say you're a dog?

619
00:38:18,760 --> 00:38:19,960
- Damn you.
- Hey!

620
00:38:21,360 --> 00:38:22,360
What's your problem?

621
00:38:22,960 --> 00:38:24,880
Do you want to have your face redone?

622
00:38:24,960 --> 00:38:26,160
Don't come near me.

623
00:38:26,760 --> 00:38:28,240
Are you going to run your mouth again?

624
00:38:28,320 --> 00:38:29,840
Hey! Stop that!

625
00:38:29,920 --> 00:38:32,000
Dam! Help me.

626
00:38:34,120 --> 00:38:35,240
What's going on?

627
00:38:35,840 --> 00:38:38,040
This madman was about to slap me.

628
00:38:39,360 --> 00:38:40,680
Bank?

629
00:38:41,480 --> 00:38:42,960
Do you guys know each other?

630
00:38:43,040 --> 00:38:44,800
He's a friend from school.

631
00:38:46,800 --> 00:38:47,880
You live around here?

632
00:38:48,920 --> 00:38:50,440
I didn't know you were a taxi biker.

633
00:38:50,520 --> 00:38:51,480
The nerve!

634
00:38:52,520 --> 00:38:53,760
Are you that good yourself?

635
00:38:55,360 --> 00:38:56,920
Though I'm just a taxi biker,

636
00:38:57,680 --> 00:38:59,400
I'm better than a felon like you.

637
00:38:59,480 --> 00:39:00,720
- Dam.
- Dammy!

638
00:39:00,800 --> 00:39:02,040
Calm down.

639
00:39:02,120 --> 00:39:04,680
It's Bank that got you expelled
from school.

640
00:39:07,720 --> 00:39:08,800
Don't make me laugh.

641
00:39:10,160 --> 00:39:12,080
Especially you.

642
00:39:13,720 --> 00:39:15,800
You got expelled,

643
00:39:15,880 --> 00:39:17,720
but you could have started over
at a new school.

644
00:39:19,400 --> 00:39:21,240
But you killed Joe.

645
00:39:22,400 --> 00:39:24,360
Can you bring him back?

646
00:39:29,560 --> 00:39:30,960
I didn't mean it.

647
00:39:32,880 --> 00:39:33,960
Save it.

648
00:39:36,040 --> 00:39:37,640
You might be free and out,

649
00:39:38,880 --> 00:39:40,560
but you are still a murderer.

650
00:39:40,640 --> 00:39:41,800
That's it.

651
00:39:41,880 --> 00:39:43,320
- Dammy!
- Dam!

652
00:39:46,160 --> 00:39:48,240
- Hey! Leave!
- Dammy!

653
00:39:51,240 --> 00:39:52,880
Let me go, murderer!

654
00:39:54,200 --> 00:39:56,040
You keep saying I'm a bad person.

655
00:39:56,120 --> 00:39:58,280
Do you think it will make you any better?

656
00:39:58,360 --> 00:40:00,280
- I don't want to hear you talk!
- Listen!

657
00:40:02,440 --> 00:40:05,160
I admit that I was wrong,

658
00:40:05,840 --> 00:40:07,720
but I'm turning over a new leaf.

659
00:40:08,480 --> 00:40:09,920
I will prove to everyone

660
00:40:10,760 --> 00:40:12,840
that a man with a criminal record

661
00:40:13,560 --> 00:40:15,240
can become a successful musician too.

662
00:40:16,560 --> 00:40:19,160
Such a hero line, Petch.

663
00:40:19,680 --> 00:40:20,520
Come here.

664
00:40:21,680 --> 00:40:23,040
Leave now.

665
00:40:25,920 --> 00:40:27,920
You don't have to tell me what to do.

666
00:40:28,000 --> 00:40:29,880
Hurry and leave, you son of a bitch.

667
00:40:40,560 --> 00:40:41,600
Oh, right.

668
00:40:42,400 --> 00:40:43,600
Don't dream too high.

669
00:40:44,520 --> 00:40:45,440
Once a felon,

670
00:40:46,600 --> 00:40:48,040
always a felon.

671
00:40:48,560 --> 00:40:50,560
- The nerve.
- Did you hear what he said? Hey!

672
00:40:50,640 --> 00:40:52,440
- Come back here!
- Dammy!

673
00:40:52,520 --> 00:40:53,680
That's enough.

674
00:40:54,280 --> 00:40:56,960
A person like him
only learns the hard way.

675
00:40:58,600 --> 00:40:59,680
Leave him be, Dam.

676
00:41:00,280 --> 00:41:01,640
His heart is weak,

677
00:41:02,480 --> 00:41:04,480
so he likes to bring others down.

678
00:41:48,760 --> 00:41:49,840
Dad!

679
00:41:51,680 --> 00:41:53,280
Is that homework?

680
00:41:56,000 --> 00:41:58,480
I have done my homework.

681
00:41:58,560 --> 00:42:00,720
- Why aren't you reading books?
- I finished reading.

682
00:42:00,800 --> 00:42:02,600
Can't you read again?

683
00:42:02,680 --> 00:42:03,680
Dad!

684
00:42:04,480 --> 00:42:05,840
I just want to dance.

685
00:42:05,920 --> 00:42:08,280
I want to become an artist when I grow up.

686
00:42:08,360 --> 00:42:09,320
In your dreams!

687
00:42:09,400 --> 00:42:11,000
Why are you doing this to me?

688
00:42:11,080 --> 00:42:13,360
What's wrong with being an artist?

689
00:42:14,600 --> 00:42:15,880
Don't be stupid.

690
00:42:16,840 --> 00:42:20,240
Those who are famous
and rich because of it aren't that many!

691
00:42:21,480 --> 00:42:23,360
The rest are just broke.

692
00:42:23,440 --> 00:42:26,760
That's not true. Believe me, Dad.

693
00:42:26,840 --> 00:42:28,520
I'll get good at dancing.

694
00:42:28,600 --> 00:42:30,240
One day, I'll provide for you.

695
00:42:30,320 --> 00:42:31,760
I told you it's nonsense.

696
00:42:32,600 --> 00:42:36,280
Why don't you want to become
an engineer, a doctor, or a manager?

697
00:42:36,880 --> 00:42:38,400
I love dancing!

698
00:42:38,480 --> 00:42:41,320
I am not letting you dance. That's final!

699
00:42:41,400 --> 00:42:44,840
No! I will dance until I die!

700
00:42:44,920 --> 00:42:46,920
Is that what you want?

701
00:42:47,000 --> 00:42:48,320
You will die as you wish!

702
00:42:52,840 --> 00:42:54,920
- Where are you going?
- Dad!

703
00:42:55,000 --> 00:42:56,400
What are you doing?

704
00:42:59,800 --> 00:43:01,960
Seriously?

705
00:43:02,040 --> 00:43:04,480
Wearing shoes inside? You'll see.

706
00:43:06,240 --> 00:43:08,000
Why are you taking my shoes, Dad?

707
00:43:08,080 --> 00:43:09,920
Don't do it, please.

708
00:43:10,000 --> 00:43:10,920
Dad!

709
00:43:11,440 --> 00:43:14,360
You can't do this, Dad.
I need my shoes for the dance.

710
00:43:14,440 --> 00:43:16,240
How will I dance now?

711
00:43:16,320 --> 00:43:18,520
So quit dancing then! Go!

712
00:43:29,640 --> 00:43:31,440
Dad!

713
00:43:33,960 --> 00:43:35,240
Dancer Shogun

714
00:43:35,760 --> 00:43:37,200
dies with this pair of shoes.

715
00:43:38,160 --> 00:43:39,040
From now on,

716
00:43:39,640 --> 00:43:40,760
you're a new person

717
00:43:41,640 --> 00:43:42,840
and have to be hardworking.

718
00:43:42,920 --> 00:43:44,360
Graduate for me.

719
00:43:56,000 --> 00:43:57,840
My shoes are all burnt.

720
00:44:03,640 --> 00:44:05,480
Why did Dad do this to me?

721
00:44:05,560 --> 00:44:06,960
So mean.

722
00:44:07,040 --> 00:44:09,200
Dad doesn't love me at all.

723
00:44:13,960 --> 00:44:15,360
I'm totally fine, Sai.

724
00:44:15,440 --> 00:44:16,480
I don't need any bandage.

725
00:44:17,080 --> 00:44:19,200
But it still needs to be cleaned.

726
00:44:19,280 --> 00:44:20,400
Sai Kaew.

727
00:44:20,480 --> 00:44:25,720
Petch, I know you're fine,
but you need to put on some ointment.

728
00:44:29,920 --> 00:44:30,920
Does it sting?

729
00:44:31,640 --> 00:44:34,160
Sai, how could it sting?

730
00:44:34,240 --> 00:44:35,320
There's no wound.

731
00:44:42,040 --> 00:44:43,640
I can't stand you!

732
00:44:43,720 --> 00:44:45,240
Dammy!

733
00:44:45,320 --> 00:44:47,800
What gives you the right
to hit me like this?

734
00:44:47,880 --> 00:44:51,240
Sai, let me ask you. Who is your brother?

735
00:44:54,800 --> 00:44:56,280
Why are you treating him?

736
00:44:57,080 --> 00:44:58,480
I can't help it.

737
00:44:58,560 --> 00:45:00,800
I'm his die-hard fan.

738
00:45:00,880 --> 00:45:03,200
Oh, you're on my nerves.
Let me throw something.

739
00:45:03,280 --> 00:45:05,760
- Here.
- Hey.

740
00:45:05,840 --> 00:45:07,000
There.

741
00:45:07,080 --> 00:45:08,480
Apply the ointment yourself.

742
00:45:08,560 --> 00:45:11,560
Losers have to heal on their own.

743
00:45:17,000 --> 00:45:18,400
Petch, where are you going?

744
00:45:20,480 --> 00:45:21,480
You keep arguing,

745
00:45:22,240 --> 00:45:23,880
so I'll play the guitar upstairs.

746
00:45:23,960 --> 00:45:25,640
Stop it right there. Come here.

747
00:45:25,720 --> 00:45:27,080
Come sit down.

748
00:45:29,840 --> 00:45:32,080
Don't leave yet. I have a question.

749
00:45:33,200 --> 00:45:34,600
What is it?

750
00:45:34,680 --> 00:45:37,360
What's up with that guy Bank?

751
00:45:37,440 --> 00:45:39,880
Why did he lose it over you?

752
00:45:40,480 --> 00:45:41,840
Back in the school days,

753
00:45:42,920 --> 00:45:44,360
Bank was Joe's sidekick.

754
00:45:44,440 --> 00:45:46,000
Joe was a bully.

755
00:45:46,760 --> 00:45:49,640
Bank followed his orders
to pick on Dam and me.

756
00:45:50,320 --> 00:45:51,440
That's right.

757
00:45:52,360 --> 00:45:54,160
Whether it's academics or music,

758
00:45:54,240 --> 00:45:56,040
he couldn't beat Petch at all,

759
00:45:56,120 --> 00:45:58,280
so he envied him.

760
00:45:59,560 --> 00:46:00,840
After the incident,

761
00:46:01,440 --> 00:46:03,160
I was sent to the training center.

762
00:46:03,240 --> 00:46:04,960
I hadn't seen him since.

763
00:46:05,920 --> 00:46:08,880
Well, it has been years, hasn't it?

764
00:46:08,960 --> 00:46:10,480
Why is he still holding a grudge?

765
00:46:13,240 --> 00:46:14,840
I'm getting goosebumps.

766
00:46:15,360 --> 00:46:17,560
What's wrong with you? Are you possessed?

767
00:46:17,640 --> 00:46:19,440
Stop with your nonsense.

768
00:46:20,280 --> 00:46:23,280
I just thought of the way
he looked at Petch.

769
00:46:23,360 --> 00:46:25,120
It gives me the chills.

770
00:46:25,640 --> 00:46:29,120
He side-eyed you like he wanted you gone.

771
00:46:29,200 --> 00:46:32,240
He must be mad because of Joe.

772
00:46:32,840 --> 00:46:34,080
That's not all.

773
00:46:35,240 --> 00:46:36,560
What do you mean?

774
00:46:36,640 --> 00:46:38,440
A failure like him

775
00:46:39,440 --> 00:46:41,960
doesn't like it when he sees me moving on.

776
00:46:42,960 --> 00:46:44,280
He wants to see me fall.

777
00:46:45,520 --> 00:46:47,160
He wants me below him.

778
00:46:47,760 --> 00:46:49,560
Then you will have to be careful.

779
00:46:50,080 --> 00:46:52,160
We don't know when he'll get back at you.

780
00:46:52,240 --> 00:46:53,680
Don't overthink it, Sai.

781
00:46:54,440 --> 00:46:55,360
It's nothing.

782
00:46:57,840 --> 00:46:58,800
Petch.

783
00:46:59,400 --> 00:47:01,960
I'm seriously worried about you.

784
00:47:02,680 --> 00:47:03,680
I know.

785
00:47:04,280 --> 00:47:05,480
I can look after myself.

786
00:47:06,520 --> 00:47:09,120
Hey, Petch. It's a big deal.

787
00:47:09,200 --> 00:47:11,680
Petch! Wait.

788
00:47:11,760 --> 00:47:13,400
If Bank talks about you--

789
00:47:16,440 --> 00:47:17,600
Hey!

790
00:47:19,760 --> 00:47:21,240
Why did you stop me?

791
00:47:21,320 --> 00:47:23,880
Why did you bring that up?

792
00:47:23,960 --> 00:47:28,160
Petch still thinks that people at work
know about him having a record.

793
00:47:28,240 --> 00:47:30,080
If he actually heard what you said,

794
00:47:30,640 --> 00:47:32,440
he would find out that we both lied!

795
00:47:33,400 --> 00:47:35,200
It's not just us two.

796
00:47:35,280 --> 00:47:37,480
Dao is also lying to him.

797
00:47:37,560 --> 00:47:38,880
Petch wouldn't be mad.

798
00:47:39,400 --> 00:47:40,960
You don't know that.

799
00:47:41,040 --> 00:47:42,840
Petch's ego is sky-high.

800
00:47:42,920 --> 00:47:45,920
If he finds out
that Dao edited his application form,

801
00:47:46,000 --> 00:47:50,080
he will blow things out of proportion
and get both of us unemployed.

802
00:47:51,320 --> 00:47:52,640
You're right.

803
00:47:53,680 --> 00:47:54,920
I'm sorry.

804
00:47:55,800 --> 00:47:59,000
Dammy, who would have thought
you had a brain?

805
00:47:59,520 --> 00:48:00,560
Of course.

806
00:48:01,080 --> 00:48:02,480
Who doesn't?

807
00:48:04,680 --> 00:48:07,320
Did she imply that I was stupid? Sai!

808
00:48:49,000 --> 00:48:51,120
I answered the questionnaire.

809
00:48:52,560 --> 00:48:55,400
I was charged with homicide.

810
00:48:55,480 --> 00:48:57,760
I know that. And?

811
00:48:58,360 --> 00:48:59,560
I don't want to hide it.

812
00:48:59,640 --> 00:49:01,520
That's why I wanted to check with you

813
00:49:01,600 --> 00:49:03,560
as a director,

814
00:49:04,080 --> 00:49:05,160
not a friend.

815
00:49:06,480 --> 00:49:07,520
A friend?

816
00:49:09,720 --> 00:49:11,080
You're engaged.

817
00:49:12,680 --> 00:49:14,200
Let's say we're ex-friends.

818
00:49:22,160 --> 00:49:23,000
<i>Dao.</i>

819
00:49:24,360 --> 00:49:25,560
<i>Isn't it funny</i>

820
00:49:26,080 --> 00:49:28,200
<i>how I'm open about my personal life,</i>

821
00:49:29,360 --> 00:49:32,440
<i>but I have to keep my feelings for you</i>

822
00:49:34,080 --> 00:49:35,880
<i>and pretend not to care about you?</i>

823
00:49:37,320 --> 00:49:40,440
<i>Do you, too, realize how different we are?</i>

824
00:49:41,480 --> 00:49:43,880
<i>How could I let you sink down to my level?</i>

825
00:49:45,240 --> 00:49:46,520
<i>Wait for me, Dao.</i>

826
00:49:47,960 --> 00:49:50,480
<i>Once I'm good enough to be by your side,</i>

827
00:49:51,560 --> 00:49:54,040
<i>I will show</i>
<i>all of my true feelings for you.</i>

828
00:50:12,760 --> 00:50:15,800
I'm a man and a man must strive.

829
00:50:16,400 --> 00:50:18,480
The pride that burdens your soul.

830
00:50:18,560 --> 00:50:19,720
Isn't it heavy?

831
00:50:19,800 --> 00:50:23,440
Bank has evidence to make Petch leave.

832
00:50:24,080 --> 00:50:25,600
I hope tomorrow

833
00:50:26,280 --> 00:50:28,480
is Petch's last day here.

834
00:50:28,560 --> 00:50:29,600
NEXT EPISODE

835
00:50:29,680 --> 00:50:30,520
Dad!

836
00:50:31,560 --> 00:50:34,200
Why did you hit Petch? You're mean!

837
00:50:34,280 --> 00:50:36,760
I suppose Natedao doesn't know about it.

838
00:50:37,360 --> 00:50:38,480
About what?

839
00:50:51,880 --> 00:50:56,800
<i>I wish I knew if I ever crossed your mind</i>

840
00:50:57,840 --> 00:51:03,080
<i>I wish I knew if you heard the whisper</i>

841
00:51:03,800 --> 00:51:09,760
<i>For my heart is crying out my love</i>
<i>It's deep and true</i>

842
00:51:09,840 --> 00:51:14,560
<i>But never reaching you</i>

843
00:51:15,800 --> 00:51:20,920
<i>I know that it simply cannot be</i>

844
00:51:21,880 --> 00:51:26,680
<i>And I never want to cause you misery</i>

845
00:51:28,320 --> 00:51:33,560
<i>I'm just an ordinary man</i>
<i>Worth nothing at all</i>

846
00:51:34,280 --> 00:51:39,600
<i>And I never want to make</i>
<i>Your teardrops fall</i>

847
00:51:41,200 --> 00:51:45,160
<i>You are out of reach</i>

848
00:51:45,840 --> 00:51:51,000
<i>Is it a crime that I need you?</i>

849
00:51:52,920 --> 00:51:57,040
<i>Please let me know for sure</i>

850
00:51:57,760 --> 00:52:03,000
<i>That you're the one I've been waiting for</i>

851
00:52:04,040 --> 00:52:08,320
<i>How much longer can I bear this pain?</i>

852
00:52:09,880 --> 00:52:14,560
<i>How much longer must I wait in vain?</i>

853
00:52:15,840 --> 00:52:21,720
<i>I really don't know what move to make</i>

854
00:52:21,800 --> 00:52:27,720
<i>To end this heartache</i>
<i>And say that I love you</i>

855
00:52:27,800 --> 00:52:29,280
Subtitle translation by: Natnaree W.
